section below for more details.
We may provide links or references to services provided by third parties whose privacy practices differ from ours. If you visit or use those services, or provide personal data to any of those third parties, their privacy policies will apply to any data shared with or collected by them.
We may disclose de-identified or aggregated information where it is not prohibited by applicable law, and we take commercially reasonable steps to maintain it in this form and to require recipients of it to do the same.
CHOICE AND CONTROL OF PERSONAL DATA
We may provide you with options and choices for how we use personal data, as described further in this section. In some jurisdictions, these options and choices may be enforceable as rights under applicable law.
Access, portability, correction, and deletion.
You can update your
in-game user
name using functionality available in our mobile game products
.  If applicable law gives you the right to request access, obtain a copy of (including for porting or transferring), correct inaccurate, or delete, personal data that we hold about you, you can make these requests by sending us an email at
support@slotslimited.com
.  When you send us an email, please note the type of request in the subject line of the email (e.g., “Request Access to Personal Data”, “Request Copy of Personal Data”, “Request Correction of Personal Data”, or “Request Deletion of Personal Data”), and if your request pertains to personal data from your use of one of our mobile game products, include your first name, last name, device identifier associated with the device you use for the mobile game product, and email address associated with your use of that mobile game product
.
If applicable law gives you the right to know additional information about our collection, use, disclosure, or sale of personal data, you can make this request by sending us an email at
support@slotslimited.com
.  Note that we have provided much of this information in this Privacy Policy.
Communication preferences. If you receive promotional email messages from us and would like to stop, you can do so by following the opt-out directions in that message. These choices do not apply to certain informational communications including surveys and mandatory service communications.
When you install our mobile game apps on your mobile device you may have the option to receive push notifications, which are messages an app sends you on your mobile device even when the app is not on. You can turn off notifications by visiting your mobile device’s “settings” page.  Our mobile game apps may also include a “your account” or “settings” section with options to turn these notifications on or off.
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information.
Some laws define “sell” and “share” very broadly, and some of our data sharing described in this Privacy Policy may be considered a “sale” or “sharing” under those definitions. In particular, third-party partners may collect name and contact information, identifiers and device information, usage data, and inferences
(each as those categories of personal data are described above in the Personal Data We Collect section) through our Services, including as further described in the
“
Cookies, Mobile IDs, and Other Technologies
”
section above.
If you do not wish for us to “sell” personal information, or “share” personal information for targeted advertising purposes, you can make your request to opt-out by
emailing us at
support@slotslimited.com
with the subject line titled
“
Do not sell my information
”
and in the email you must write your name, the name of the game whose account you do not want the information shared or sold, the platform you are using to play the game (Android or iOS), and your user ID
.
If you opt-out using these choices, we will take steps to stop disclosing personal data in ways that are considered a “sale” or “sharing” (for targeted advertising) for which opt-out rights are required under applicable law. However, we will continue to disclose personal information to service providers and others as allowed by applicable law. We do not knowingly sell or share personal data of minors under 16 years of age.
Targeted advertising. To opt-out from having personal data we collect from you in connection with our Services used for targeted advertising, you can use the:
·
In-App Settings
contain a menu where you may toggle
“
On
”
or
“
Off
”
targeted advertising titled
“
Do Not Sell My Personal Information
”
·
Global Privacy Control
(“GPC”) setting in a web browser or browser extension, which advertising-related Technologies on our website may honor. Web browsers and browser extensions that support the GPC setting may send a signal to the websites you visit indicating your choice to opt-out from “sales” of personal information and/or targeted advertising. When we detect such a signal, we will make reasonable efforts to respect your choices as communicated by the GPC signal where it is recognized by applicable law as a valid opt-out preference signal.
Note, the GPC is not designed for mobile apps, and for that reason, will not impact practices for our gaming app products.
Other options may also be available to help reduce targeted advertising, but may not prevent having personal data we, and the third-party partners we work with, collect from you being used for targeted advertising. These options include:
·
Industry opt-out tools
. These include the NAI (
http://optout.networkadvertising.org
), DAA (
http://optout.aboutads.info/
), and European DAA (
http://www.youronlinechoices.com/
)
·
Cookie controls
. Most web browsers are set to accept cookies by default. If you prefer, you can go to your browser settings to learn how to delete or reject cookies. If you choose to delete or reject cookies, this could affect certain features or services of our website. If you choose to delete cookies, settings and preferences controlled by those cookies, including advertising preferences, may be deleted and may need to be recreated.
·
Do Not Track
. Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" (DNT) setting that can send a signal to the websites you visit indicating you do not wish to be tracked. Unlike the GPC signals described above, there is not a common understanding of how to interpret the DNT signal; therefore,
our Services do not respond to browser DNT signals
.
·
Mobile advertising ID controls
. iOS and Android operating systems may provide options to limit tracking and/or reset advertising IDs commonly used to help targeted advertising.
All of the options in this section are specific to the device or browser you are using. If you access our services from other devices or browsers, take these actions from those devices and browsers as well.
Email web beacons. Most email clients have settings that allow you to prevent the automatic downloading of images, including web beacons, and the automatic connection to the web servers that host those images.
Consent. Where applicable law requires us to have a lawful basis for processing your personal data, and we process personal data based solely on your consent, you can make a request to withdraw consent for future processing based on your rights under applicable law by sending us an email at
support@slotslimited.com
.  When you send us an email, please note “Request to Withdraw Consent” in the subject line of the email, and if your request pertains to personal data from your use of one of our mobile game products, include your first name, last name,
the specific name of the game you are requesting to withdraw your consent from, the platform of the game (Android or iOS), your user ID
, and email address associated with your use of that mobile game product
.
Objecting to or restricting processing.  Where applicable law requires us to have a lawful basis for processing your personal data, and we process personal data based solely on our legitimate interests, you can make a request that objects to processing based on your rights under applicable law by sending us an email at
support@slotslimited.com
.  When you send us an email, please note “Request to Restrict Processing” in the subject line of the email, and if your request pertains to personal data from your use of one of our mobile game products, include your first name, last name,
the specific name of the game you are requesting to withdraw your consent from, the platform of the game (Android or iOS), your user ID
, and email address associated with your use of that mobile game product
.
Except for the automated controls described above, if you send us a request to exercise choices noted in this section, to the extent permitted by applicable law, we may decline requests in certain cases. For example, we may decline requests where we are unable to authenticate you as the person to whom the personal data relates.  We also may decline requests where it: would be prohibited by law; could adversely affect the privacy or other rights of another person; would reveal a trade secret or other confidential information; would interfere with a legal or business obligation that requires retention or use of the data; is unreasonable or excessive; or where applicable law does not require us to do so. If you receive a response from us informing you that we have declined your request, in whole or in part, you may appeal that decision by submitting your appeal using the contact method described at the bottom of this Privacy Policy. In Europe, you may also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, but we encourage you to first contact us with any questions or concerns.
You may designate, in writing or through a power of attorney, an authorized agent to make requests on your behalf to exercise your rights where permitted by law. Before accepting such a request from an agent, we will require the agent to provide proof you have authorized it to act on your behalf, and we may need you to verify your identity directly with us.
For certain requests we will need to verify your identity to the degree of certainty required by law. For example we may verify your request by asking you to send it from the email address associated with your
Slots Limited game account, with your in-game User ID listed, the name of the a
or requiring you to provide information necessary to verify your account or use of our mobile game products.
You have a right to not be discriminated against for exercising your rights under applicable law, including where applicable, when making the requests noted above.
EUROPEAN DATA PROTECTION RIGHTS
If the processing of personal data about you is subject to European Union data protection law, you have the right to: request access to, and rectification or erasure of, personal data; receive a copy of personal data about you in a usable and portable format (if it is subject to automated processing based on your consent or a contract with you); withdraw your consent for future personal data processing based on your consent; and object to or request restriction of processing of your personal data under certain circumstances.  To make a request regarding any of these rights, see the Choice and Control of Personal Data section above.
We rely on different lawful bases for collecting and processing personal data about you, for example, with your consent and/or as necessary to provide the services you use, operate our business, meet our contractual and legal obligations, protect the security of our systems and our customers, or fulfil other legitimate interests.
U.S. STATE PRIVACY RIGHTS AND NOTICES
If you are a resident of California
, Colorado, Connecticut, Oregon, Texas, Utah, Virginia, or another U.S. state with a comprehensive data privacy law in effect, you may have the right to: know information about personal data we collect, use, disclose, or sell about you; request correction or deletion of personal data; opt-out of “sales” or “sharing” (for targeted advertising) of personal data; request that we limit the use of sensitive personal data other than to provide you with the services you request or as permitted by law (note, we do not use sensitive personal data as defined under applicable law for such additional purposes)
We do not knowingly “sell” or “share” (for targeted advertising) personal data of minors under 16 years of age.
Under California Civil Code section 1798.83, California residents who have provided personal information to a business with which the individual has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes may request information about whether the business has disclosed personal information to any third parties for the third parties’ direct marketing purposes.  We do not disclose personal information to any third parties for their direct marketing purposes as defined by this law.
RETENTION OF PERSONAL DATA
We retain personal data for as long as necessary to provide the services and fulfill the transactions you have requested, comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, enforce our agreements, and for other legitimate and lawful business purposes. Because these needs can vary for different data types in the context of different services and business practices, actual retention periods can vary significantly based on criteria such as your expectations or consent, the sensitivity of the personal data, options you have to delete or request deletion of the data, and our legal obligations.
LOCATION OF PERSONAL DATA
The personal data we collect may be stored and processed in your country or region, or in any other country where we or our affiliates, subsidiaries, or service providers process data, some of which may have laws that offer different levels of data protection than the country in which you reside. We take steps to help process personal data as described in this Privacy Policy wherever the data is located.
LOCATION OF PROCESSING PESRONAL DATA (EUROPE)
For territories and countries including the UK, Switzerland, and the European Economic Area where there are regulations on providing protection for personal information when data is transferred from these territories and countries to anywhere else, we use measures as stipulated by the European Commission and other regulations from the UK
’
s Secretary of State.
When a data transfer occurs and is not subject to such regulations, similar measures are taken to protect personal information that are in accordance with applicable laws and this Privacy Policy, the
European Commission
’
s Standard Contractual Clauses
under Article 46(2) which includes the UK Addendum for
transferring
data which originates from the UK.
SECURITY OF PERSONAL DATA
We take commercially reasonable steps to help protect personal data from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
We will update this Privacy Policy when necessary to reflect changes in our Services, how we use personal data, or the applicable law. When we post changes to the Privacy Policy, we will revise the "Last Updated" date at the top of the Privacy Policy. If we make material changes to the Privacy Policy, we will provide notice or obtain consent regarding such changes as may be required by law.
HOW TO CONTACT US
If you have a privacy concern, complaint, or a question for us, please contact us at
support@slotslimited.com
