COOKIES, MOBILE IDs,
AND OTHER TECHNOLOGIES
We, or service providers, and third-party partners use cookies, web beacons, mobile analytics and advertising IDs, and other technologies (collectively, “Technologies”) to operate our Services and to help collect information, including the types of identifiers and device information, and usage data, described above.
What are cookies, mobile IDs, and other technologies?
Cookies are small text files placed by a website and stored by your browser on your device. A cookie can later be read when your browser connects to a web server in the same domain that placed the cookie.
The text in a cookie contains a string of numbers and letters that may uniquely identify your device and can contain other information as well. This allows the web server to recognize your browser over time, each time it connects to that web server.
Web beacons are electronic images (also called pixels or clear GIFs) that are contained within a website or email. When your browser opens a webpage or email that contains a web beacon, it automatically connects to the web server that hosts the image (typically operated by a third party). This allows that web server to log information about your device and to set and read its own cookies. In the same way, third-party content on our websites (such as embedded videos, plug-ins, or ads) results in your browser connecting to the third-party web server that hosts that content.
Mobile analytics and advertising IDs are generated by operating systems for mobile devices (including those that use iOS and Android operating systems).  These can be accessed and used by apps like our mobile game products. Our mobile game products contain software that enables us and our third-party partners and service providers to access these mobile analytics and advertising IDs.
How do we and our partners use cookies, mobile IDs, and other technologies?
We, our service providers, and companies acting as third parties (“third-party partners”), each use Technologies in our Services to collect personal data and other information (such as the pages you visit, the links you click on, and similar usage information, identifiers, and device information) when you use our Services, including personal data about your online activities over time and across different websites or online services.
We, and our third-party partners and service providers, use personal data and other information collected from Technologies for a variety of purposes, such as to store your preferences and settings, enable you to sign-in, analyze how our websites and mobile game products perform, track your interaction with the site or mobile game product, develop inferences, deliver and tailor interest-based advertising, combat fraud, and fulfill other legitimate purposes. We and/or our third-party partners and service providers also share the data we collect or infer with third parties for these purposes.
Third-party partners use personal data and other information collected from Technologies for our purposes and other purposes. Third-party partners may use and combine this data across multiple sites for their own and third party purposes.  For example, we use Google Analytics on our website to help us understand how users interact with our website; you can learn how Google collects and uses information at
www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners
. Some of the data disclosures to these third-party partners may be considered a “sale” or “sharing” of personal data as defined under certain U.S. state laws. Please see the
“Choice and Control of Personal Information”
and
“Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information”
sections below for more details.
For more information about the types of third-party partners and service providers that collect personal data via our Services, please see the
“Our Disclosure of Personal Data
”
section of this Privacy Policy.
What controls are available?
There are a range of cookie and related controls available through browsers, mobile operating systems, and elsewhere. See the
“Choice and Control of Personal Data
”
section below for details.
